☕ Java Instance Variables and Static Variables Practice Questions (Basic → Advanced)
🟢 1. Instance Variable

Create a Student class with instance variables id and name. Create two objects and print their values.

🟢 2. Static Variable

Create a Student class with a static variable collegeName = "ABC College" and display it for three students.

🟢 3. Instance vs Static

Create a Car class with:

Instance variables: brand, price
Static variable: company = "Toyota"

Create two objects and print all details.

🟡 4. Object Counter

Create a class Employee with a static variable count that stores the total number of objects created.

🟡 5. Shared Data

Create a BankAccount class with:

Instance variables: accountNo, balance
Static variable: bankName

Create three accounts and display the details.

🟡 6. Change Static Variable

Create a School class with a static variable schoolName. Change its value and show that the change is reflected in all objects.

🟠 7. Product Management

Create a Product class with:

Instance variables: productName, price
Static variable: discount = 10

Calculate and print the final price after applying the discount.

🔴 8. Student Counter

Create a Student class where every new object increases a static variable studentCount. Print the total count after creating 5 students.

🔴 9. Library System

Create a LibraryBook class with:

Instance variables: bookId, bookName
Static variable: libraryName

Create multiple book objects and display their details.

🏆 10. University Management (Advanced)

Create a University class with:

Static variable: universityName
Instance variables: studentId, studentName, course

Create at least 3 student objects, display all details, and demonstrate that:

Each object has its own instance variable values.
All objects share the same static variable value.